{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":328,"text":"The writer George Eliot cautioned us that,"},{"time":3277,"text":"among all forms of mistake,"},{"time":5344,"text":"prophesy is the most gratuitous."},{"time":7707,"text":"The person that we would all acknowledge"},{"time":9555,"text":"as her 20th-century counterpart, Yogi Berra, agreed."},{"time":13857,"text":"He said, \"It's tough to make predictions,"},{"time":15722,"text":"especially about the future.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":18458,"text":"I'm going to ignore their cautions"},{"time":20269,"text":"and make one very specific forecast."},{"time":22242,"text":"In the world that we are creating very quickly,"},{"time":24882,"text":"we're going to see more and more things"},{"time":26595,"text":"that look like science fiction,"},{"time":28320,"text":"and fewer and fewer things that look like jobs."},{"time":31436,"text":"Our cars are very quickly going to start driving themselves,"},{"time":34188,"text":"which means we're going to need fewer truck drivers."},{"time":36884,"text":"We're going to hook Siri up to Watson"},{"time":39005,"text":"and use that to automate a lot of the work"},{"time":41602,"text":"that's currently done by customer service reps"},{"time":43828,"text":"and troubleshooters and diagnosers,"},{"time":46732,"text":"and we're already taking R2D2,"},{"time":48988,"text":"painting him orange, and putting him to work"},{"time":52228,"text":"carrying shelves around warehouses,"},{"time":54777,"text":"which means we need a lot fewer people"},{"time":56852,"text":"to be walking up and down those aisles."}]},{"cues":[{"time":58818,"text":"Now, for about 200 years,"},{"time":62620,"text":"people have been saying exactly what I'm telling you --"},{"time":64803,"text":"the age of technological unemployment is at hand —"},{"time":67620,"text":"starting with the Luddites smashing looms in Britain"},{"time":70035,"text":"just about two centuries ago,"},{"time":71931,"text":"and they have been wrong."},{"time":73963,"text":"Our economies in the developed world have coasted along"},{"time":76780,"text":"on something pretty close to full employment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":78714,"text":"Which brings up a critical question:"},{"time":80813,"text":"Why is this time different, if it really is?"},{"time":83739,"text":"The reason it's different is that, just in the past few years,"},{"time":86735,"text":"our machines have started demonstrating skills"},{"time":88630,"text":"they have never, ever had before:"},{"time":91255,"text":"understanding, speaking, hearing, seeing,"},{"time":94515,"text":"answering, writing, and they're still acquiring new skills."},{"time":98728,"text":"For example, mobile humanoid robots"},{"time":101298,"text":"are still incredibly primitive,"},{"time":103245,"text":"but the research arm of the Defense Department"},{"time":105083,"text":"just launched a competition"},{"time":106598,"text":"to have them do things like this,"},{"time":108912,"text":"and if the track record is any guide,"},{"time":110645,"text":"this competition is going to be successful."},{"time":113044,"text":"So when I look around, I think the day is not too far off at all"},{"time":116680,"text":"when we're going to have androids"},{"time":118856,"text":"doing a lot of the work that we are doing right now."},{"time":121737,"text":"And we're creating a world where there is going to be"},{"time":125495,"text":"more and more technology and fewer and fewer jobs."},{"time":129180,"text":"It's a world that Erik Brynjolfsson and I are calling"},{"time":131429,"text":"\"the new machine age.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":132920,"text":"The thing to keep in mind is that"},{"time":135053,"text":"this is absolutely great news."},{"time":137602,"text":"This is the best economic news on the planet these days."},{"time":140919,"text":"Not that there's a lot of competition, right?"},{"time":144448,"text":"This is the best economic news we have these days"},{"time":146347,"text":"for two main reasons."},{"time":147963,"text":"The first is, technological progress is what allows us"},{"time":150948,"text":"to continue this amazing recent run that we're on"},{"time":154685,"text":"where output goes up over time,"},{"time":157206,"text":"while at the same time, prices go down,"},{"time":160532,"text":"and volume and quality just continue to explode."},{"time":164736,"text":"Now, some people look at this and talk about"},{"time":166737,"text":"shallow materialism,"},{"time":168143,"text":"but that's absolutely the wrong way to look at it."},{"time":170561,"text":"This is abundance, which is exactly"},{"time":173056,"text":"what we want our economic system to provide."},{"time":176478,"text":"The second reason that the new machine age"},{"time":179694,"text":"is such great news is that, once the androids"},{"time":182000,"text":"start doing jobs, we don't have to do them anymore,"},{"time":185252,"text":"and we get freed up from drudgery and toil."}]},{"cues":[{"time":189008,"text":"Now, when I talk about this with my friends"},{"time":191032,"text":"in Cambridge and Silicon Valley, they say,"},{"time":193584,"text":"\"Fantastic. No more drudgery, no more toil."},{"time":195857,"text":"This gives us the chance to imagine"},{"time":197908,"text":"an entirely different kind of society,"},{"time":200201,"text":"a society where the creators and the discoverers"},{"time":203113,"text":"and the performers and the innovators"},{"time":204942,"text":"come together with their patrons and their financiers"},{"time":208451,"text":"to talk about issues, entertain, enlighten,"},{"time":211130,"text":"provoke each other.\""},{"time":213208,"text":"It's a society really, that looks a lot like the TED Conference."},{"time":217783,"text":"And there's actually a huge amount of truth here."},{"time":220266,"text":"We are seeing an amazing flourishing taking place."},{"time":223289,"text":"In a world where it is just about as easy"},{"time":225291,"text":"to generate an object as it is to print a document,"},{"time":228698,"text":"we have amazing new possibilities."},{"time":230787,"text":"The people who used to be craftsmen and hobbyists"},{"time":234464,"text":"are now makers, and they're responsible"},{"time":236331,"text":"for massive amounts of innovation."},{"time":238721,"text":"And artists who were formerly constrained"},{"time":241003,"text":"can now do things that were never, ever possible"},{"time":244171,"text":"for them before."},{"time":246067,"text":"So this is a time of great flourishing,"},{"time":248184,"text":"and the more I look around, the more convinced I become"},{"time":251116,"text":"that this quote, from the physicist Freeman Dyson,"},{"time":254190,"text":"is not hyperbole at all."},{"time":256223,"text":"This is just a plain statement of the facts."},{"time":259013,"text":"We are in the middle of an astonishing period."}]},{"cues":[{"time":260858,"text":"[\"Technology is a gift of God. After the gift of life it is perhaps the greatest of God's gifts. It is the mother of civilizations, of arts and of sciences.\" — Freeman Dyson]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":261742,"text":"Which brings up another great question:"},{"time":264533,"text":"What could possibly go wrong in this new machine age?"},{"time":267509,"text":"Right? Great, hang up, flourish, go home."},{"time":270871,"text":"We're going to face two really thorny sets of challenges"},{"time":273537,"text":"as we head deeper into the future that we're creating."}]},{"cues":[{"time":276330,"text":"The first are economic, and they're really nicely summarized"},{"time":279580,"text":"in an apocryphal story about a back-and-forth"},{"time":282670,"text":"between Henry Ford II and Walter Reuther,"},{"time":285712,"text":"who was the head of the auto workers union."},{"time":288457,"text":"They were touring one of the new modern factories,"},{"time":290640,"text":"and Ford playfully turns to Reuther and says,"},{"time":293390,"text":"\"Hey Walter, how are you going to get these robots"},{"time":295552,"text":"to pay union dues?\""},{"time":297366,"text":"And Reuther shoots back, \"Hey Henry,"},{"time":299311,"text":"how are you going to get them to buy cars?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":303853,"text":"Reuther's problem in that anecdote"},{"time":306864,"text":"is that it is tough to offer your labor to an economy"},{"time":310973,"text":"that's full of machines,"},{"time":312608,"text":"and we see this very clearly in the statistics."},{"time":314832,"text":"If you look over the past couple decades"},{"time":317224,"text":"at the returns to capital -- in other words, corporate profits --"},{"time":320888,"text":"we see them going up,"},{"time":322572,"text":"and we see that they're now at an all-time high."},{"time":324659,"text":"If we look at the returns to labor, in other words"},{"time":327360,"text":"total wages paid out in the economy,"},{"time":329244,"text":"we see them at an all-time low"},{"time":331791,"text":"and heading very quickly in the opposite direction."}]},{"cues":[{"time":334856,"text":"So this is clearly bad news for Reuther."},{"time":336626,"text":"It looks like it might be great news for Ford,"},{"time":340024,"text":"but it's actually not. If you want to sell"},{"time":342328,"text":"huge volumes of somewhat expensive goods to people,"},{"time":345672,"text":"you really want a large, stable, prosperous middle class."},{"time":349460,"text":"We have had one of those in America"},{"time":351684,"text":"for just about the entire postwar period."},{"time":354317,"text":"But the middle class is clearly under huge threat right now."},{"time":358669,"text":"We all know a lot of the statistics,"},{"time":360080,"text":"but just to repeat one of them,"},{"time":362439,"text":"median income in America has actually gone down"},{"time":365206,"text":"over the past 15 years,"},{"time":366897,"text":"and we're in danger of getting trapped"},{"time":368612,"text":"in some vicious cycle where inequality and polarization"},{"time":372537,"text":"continue to go up over time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":375717,"text":"The societal challenges that come along"},{"time":378116,"text":"with that kind of inequality deserve some attention."},{"time":380692,"text":"There are a set of societal challenges"},{"time":382360,"text":"that I'm actually not that worried about,"},{"time":384304,"text":"and they're captured by images like this."},{"time":386655,"text":"This is not the kind of societal problem"},{"time":388477,"text":"that I am concerned about."},{"time":390941,"text":"There is no shortage of dystopian visions"},{"time":393084,"text":"about what happens when our machines become self-aware,"},{"time":396567,"text":"and they decide to rise up and coordinate attacks against us."},{"time":399743,"text":"I'm going to start worrying about those"},{"time":401490,"text":"the day my computer becomes aware of my printer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":404719,"text":"(Laughter) (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":408348,"text":"So this is not the set of challenges we really need to worry about."},{"time":411320,"text":"To tell you the kinds of societal challenges"},{"time":414108,"text":"that are going to come up in the new machine age,"},{"time":416320,"text":"I want to tell a story about two stereotypical American workers."},{"time":420031,"text":"And to make them really stereotypical,"},{"time":421799,"text":"let's make them both white guys."},{"time":423946,"text":"And the first one is a college-educated"},{"time":427708,"text":"professional, creative type, manager,"},{"time":430854,"text":"engineer, doctor, lawyer, that kind of worker."},{"time":433605,"text":"We're going to call him \"Ted.\""},{"time":436024,"text":"He's at the top of the American middle class."},{"time":438297,"text":"His counterpart is not college-educated"},{"time":441179,"text":"and works as a laborer, works as a clerk,"},{"time":444243,"text":"does low-level white collar or blue collar work in the economy."},{"time":447555,"text":"We're going to call that guy \"Bill.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":449960,"text":"And if you go back about 50 years,"},{"time":452039,"text":"Bill and Ted were leading remarkably similar lives."},{"time":455856,"text":"For example, in 1960 they were both very likely"},{"time":458359,"text":"to have full-time jobs, working at least 40 hours a week."},{"time":461729,"text":"But as the social researcher Charles Murray has documented,"},{"time":465025,"text":"as we started to automate the economy,"},{"time":467993,"text":"and 1960 is just about when computers started to be used by businesses,"},{"time":472140,"text":"as we started to progressively inject technology"},{"time":475011,"text":"and automation and digital stuff into the economy,"},{"time":477747,"text":"the fortunes of Bill and Ted diverged a lot."},{"time":480772,"text":"Over this time frame, Ted has continued"},{"time":482891,"text":"to hold a full-time job. Bill hasn't."},{"time":485643,"text":"In many cases, Bill has left the economy entirely,"},{"time":489914,"text":"and Ted very rarely has."},{"time":492178,"text":"Over time, Ted's marriage has stayed quite happy."},{"time":495443,"text":"Bill's hasn't."},{"time":497084,"text":"And Ted's kids have grown up in a two-parent home,"},{"time":500406,"text":"while Bill's absolutely have not over time."},{"time":503626,"text":"Other ways that Bill is dropping out of society?"},{"time":506030,"text":"He's decreased his voting in presidential elections,"},{"time":509719,"text":"and he's started to go to prison a lot more often."},{"time":513712,"text":"So I cannot tell a happy story about these social trends,"},{"time":517696,"text":"and they don't show any signs of reversing themselves."},{"time":520443,"text":"They're also true no matter which ethnic group"},{"time":523416,"text":"or demographic group we look at,"},{"time":525137,"text":"and they're actually getting so severe"},{"time":527213,"text":"that they're in danger of overwhelming"},{"time":528984,"text":"even the amazing progress we made with the Civil Rights Movement."}]},{"cues":[{"time":532632,"text":"And what my friends in Silicon Valley"},{"time":535144,"text":"and Cambridge are overlooking is that they're Ted."},{"time":540395,"text":"They're living these amazingly busy, productive lives,"},{"time":543832,"text":"and they've got all the benefits to show from that,"},{"time":546222,"text":"while Bill is leading a very different life."},{"time":548657,"text":"They're actually both proof of how right Voltaire was"},{"time":550797,"text":"when he talked about the benefits of work,"},{"time":553049,"text":"and the fact that it saves us from not one but three great evils."}]},{"cues":[{"time":556630,"text":"[\"Work saves a man from three great evils: boredom, vice and need.\" — Voltaire]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":557627,"text":"So with these challenges, what do we do about them?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":560963,"text":"The economic playbook is surprisingly clear,"},{"time":563546,"text":"surprisingly straightforward, in the short term especially."},{"time":566686,"text":"The robots are not going to take all of our jobs in the next year or two,"},{"time":569578,"text":"so the classic Econ 101 playbook is going to work just fine:"},{"time":574046,"text":"Encourage entrepreneurship,"},{"time":576198,"text":"double down on infrastructure,"},{"time":578394,"text":"and make sure we're turning out people"},{"time":580093,"text":"from our educational system with the appropriate skills."}]},{"cues":[{"time":583690,"text":"But over the longer term, if we are moving into an economy"},{"time":586967,"text":"that's heavy on technology and light on labor,"},{"time":589619,"text":"and we are, then we have to consider"},{"time":592047,"text":"some more radical interventions,"},{"time":593831,"text":"for example, something like a guaranteed minimum income."},{"time":597030,"text":"Now, that's probably making some folk in this room uncomfortable,"},{"time":600742,"text":"because that idea is associated with the extreme left wing"},{"time":604599,"text":"and with fairly radical schemes for redistributing wealth."},{"time":607818,"text":"I did a little bit of research on this notion,"},{"time":609771,"text":"and it might calm some folk down to know that"},{"time":612226,"text":"the idea of a net guaranteed minimum income"},{"time":614858,"text":"has been championed by those frothing-at-the-mouth socialists"},{"time":618035,"text":"Friedrich Hayek, Richard Nixon and Milton Friedman."},{"time":623508,"text":"And if you find yourself worried"},{"time":625387,"text":"that something like a guaranteed income"},{"time":628696,"text":"is going to stifle our drive to succeed"},{"time":630971,"text":"and make us kind of complacent,"},{"time":632735,"text":"you might be interested to know that social mobility,"},{"time":635525,"text":"one of the things we really pride ourselves on in the United States,"},{"time":638200,"text":"is now lower than it is in the northern European countries"},{"time":641540,"text":"that have these very generous social safety nets."},{"time":644739,"text":"So the economic playbook is actually pretty straightforward."}]},{"cues":[{"time":647531,"text":"The societal one is a lot more challenging."},{"time":650587,"text":"I don't know what the playbook is"},{"time":652735,"text":"for getting Bill to engage and stay engaged throughout life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":656563,"text":"I do know that education is a huge part of it."},{"time":659067,"text":"I witnessed this firsthand."},{"time":660847,"text":"I was a Montessori kid for the first few years of my education,"},{"time":664603,"text":"and what that education taught me"},{"time":666132,"text":"is that the world is an interesting place"},{"time":668223,"text":"and my job is to go explore it."},{"time":670864,"text":"The school stopped in third grade,"},{"time":672565,"text":"so then I entered the public school system,"},{"time":674633,"text":"and it felt like I had been sent to the Gulag."},{"time":678999,"text":"With the benefit of hindsight, I now know the job"},{"time":681900,"text":"was to prepare me for life as a clerk or a laborer,"},{"time":684414,"text":"but at the time it felt like the job was to kind of"},{"time":686744,"text":"bore me into some submission with what was going on around me."},{"time":690568,"text":"We have to do better than this."},{"time":691916,"text":"We cannot keep turning out Bills."}]},{"cues":[{"time":695592,"text":"So we see some green shoots that things are getting better."},{"time":697936,"text":"We see technology deeply impacting education"},{"time":700760,"text":"and engaging people, from our youngest learners"},{"time":703288,"text":"up to our oldest ones."},{"time":705052,"text":"We see very prominent business voices telling us"},{"time":707672,"text":"we need to rethink some of the things that we've been holding dear for a while."},{"time":710888,"text":"And we see very serious and sustained"},{"time":713148,"text":"and data-driven efforts to understand"},{"time":715952,"text":"how to intervene in some of the most troubled communities that we have."}]},{"cues":[{"time":719495,"text":"So the green shoots are out there."},{"time":721704,"text":"I don't want to pretend for a minute"},{"time":723138,"text":"that what we have is going to be enough."},{"time":725080,"text":"We're facing very tough challenges."},{"time":727222,"text":"To give just one example, there are about five million Americans"},{"time":730328,"text":"who have been unemployed for at least six months."},{"time":733142,"text":"We're not going to fix things for them"},{"time":734484,"text":"by sending them back to Montessori."},{"time":736927,"text":"And my biggest worry is that we're creating a world"},{"time":739282,"text":"where we're going to have glittering technologies"},{"time":741831,"text":"embedded in kind of a shabby society"},{"time":744136,"text":"and supported by an economy that generates inequality"},{"time":747103,"text":"instead of opportunity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":748584,"text":"But I actually don't think that's what we're going to do."},{"time":751336,"text":"I think we're going to do something a lot better"},{"time":752965,"text":"for one very straightforward reason:"},{"time":755075,"text":"The facts are getting out there."},{"time":757043,"text":"The realities of this new machine age"},{"time":759085,"text":"and the change in the economy are becoming more widely known."},{"time":762400,"text":"If we wanted to accelerate that process, we could do things"},{"time":765251,"text":"like have our best economists and policymakers"},{"time":768017,"text":"play \"Jeopardy!\" against Watson."},{"time":770436,"text":"We could send Congress on an autonomous car road trip."},{"time":773986,"text":"And if we do enough of these kinds of things,"},{"time":775639,"text":"the awareness is going to sink in that things are going to be different."},{"time":779043,"text":"And then we're off to the races,"},{"time":780814,"text":"because I don't believe for a second"},{"time":783244,"text":"that we have forgotten how to solve tough challenges"},{"time":786212,"text":"or that we have become too apathetic or hard-hearted to even try."}]},{"cues":[{"time":790562,"text":"I started my talk with quotes from wordsmiths"},{"time":792956,"text":"who were separated by an ocean and a century."},{"time":795772,"text":"Let me end it with words from politicians"},{"time":797924,"text":"who were similarly distant."}]},{"cues":[{"time":799655,"text":"Winston Churchill came to my home of MIT in 1949,"},{"time":802988,"text":"and he said, \"If we are to bring the broad masses"},{"time":805136,"text":"of the people in every land to the table of abundance,"},{"time":808846,"text":"it can only be by the tireless improvement"},{"time":811876,"text":"of all of our means of technical production.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":814849,"text":"Abraham Lincoln realized there was one other ingredient."},{"time":817468,"text":"He said, \"I am a firm believer in the people."},{"time":820366,"text":"If given the truth, they can be depended upon"},{"time":822699,"text":"to meet any national crisis."},{"time":825068,"text":"The great point is to give them the plain facts.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":827852,"text":"So the optimistic note, great point that I want to leave you with"},{"time":830962,"text":"is that the plain facts of the machine age are becoming clear,"},{"time":834107,"text":"and I have every confidence that we're going to use them"},{"time":836564,"text":"to chart a good course into the challenging,"},{"time":839479,"text":"abundant economy that we're creating."}]},{"cues":[{"time":842012,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":843703,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}